Time Complexity:

Let n = size of array  
Let d = number of digits in each number

    Traverse each number → O(n)
    Extract digits → O(d)

Overall: O(n * d)


Space Complexity:

    No extra space used

Overall: O(1)


Approach:

1. Initialize count = 0

2. Traverse each element in array:

   - While number > 0:
     → Extract last digit using (num % 10)
     → If it equals given digit → increment count
     → Remove last digit (num = num / 10)

3. Repeat for all elements

4. Return total count





class Solution {
    public int countDigitOccurrences(int[] nums, int digit) {
        int count = 0;
        for(int ele: nums){
            while(ele>0){
                if(digit == ele%10) count++;
                ele/=10;
            }
        }
        return count;
    }
}
